Embedding:

Embedding is the process of converting text, images, or other data into high-dimensional numerical vectors that capture their semantic meaning.

Vector Database:

A Vector Database stores embeddings and performs similarity search to retrieve the most semantically relevant data. It is widely used in RAG systems, semantic search, recommendation systems, and AI agents.

RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)

RAG ek technique hai jisme AI answer dene se pehle relevant data search karta hai, phir us data ko use karke answer generate karta hai.

Short Flow
User Question
      ↓
Embedding
      ↓
Vector Database Search
      ↓
Relevant Documents
      ↓
LLM (Gemini/GPT)
      ↓
Final Answer
Example

User: "Company ki leave policy kya hai?"

Without RAG: AI → "I don't know."
With RAG: AI → Company ke documents search karega → Leave Policy PDF milegi → Uske basis par sahi answer dega.
One-line Definition

RAG = Search first, Answer later.